722399f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 125th Street
722399f-a.text:
1821 Park Avenue, N. E. corner 125th Street, at that time known as
2303 Fourth Avenue, an old frame house, which stood on this site
till about 1900, when it was replaced by 12-story Hamilton Build-
ing -later known as Lee Building.
About 1873.

715372f-a.title: Manhattan: 125th Street - Park Avenue
715372f-a.text:
103-125 East 125th Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner
of Park Ave. The Lee Building (12-story), is shown directly at the corner
proper. Note Loew's Orpheum and the Majestic Hall, both housed in the old
Harlem Hall (Nos. 117-125).
1904.
International News Photos Iio.
N.~132I

715373f-a.title: Manhattan: 125th Street - Park Avenue
715373f-a.text:
79-81 East 125th Street, adjoining and at the N.W. corner of Park Ave.
The Mt. Morris Branch of the Corn Exchange Bank is shown employing the
lower floors of corner building (No. 81), also known as No. 1820 Park Ave.
A portion of the 125th Street Station of the N.Y.C.R.R., is also shown on
Park Ave.
June 24, 1934.
L. Sperr.

715371f-a.title: Manhattan: 125th Street - Park Avenue
715371f-a.text:
East 125th Street, east from, but not including Park Ave. Notice
the Harlem Grand Theatre, (Nos. 117-125) and Proctor's 125th Street Theatre,
(Nos. 112-118) facing each other on opposite sides of the street.
July 24, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

715370f-b.title: Manhattan: 125th Street - Park Avenue
715370f-b.text:
The Hotel Naomi, 125th Street at the S.W. corner of Park Ave.
This hotel, facing on Park Ave., is composed of five brick houses
joined together. Its sale was recently delayed to locate the owner
of a four-inch strip through the centre.
August 2, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
The same, from a different angle.
July 24, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

722401f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 125th Street
